        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 6:16PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 616 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 10 miles north of Billings West End to
10 miles north of Joliet, or extending from 11 miles northwest of
Billings to 14 miles east of Columbus, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pockets of half inch size hail
with the strongest storms.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Billings, Laurel, Billings West End, Billings Heights, Lockwood,
Shepherd, Huntley, Acton, Park City and Crow Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
